5 594 M
(1.   22.1.1.3 [lib.locale.members] locale::combine should be const) s
5 572 M
(locale::combine is the only member function of locale \(other) s
5 561 M
(than constructors and destructor\) that is not const.  There is) s
5 550 M
(no reason for it not to be const, and good reasons why it should) s
5 539 M
(have been const.  Furthermore, leaving it non-const conflicts) s
5 528 M
(with 22.1.1 paragraph 6: "An instance of a locale is immutable.") s
5 506 M
(History: this member function originally was a constructor.) s
5 495 M
(it happened that the interface it specified had no corresponding) s
5 484 M
(language syntax, so it was changed to a member function.) s
5 473 M
(As constructors are never const, there was no "const" in) s
5 462 M
(the interface which was transformed into member "combine".) s
5 451 M
(It should have been added at that time, but the omission was) s
5 440 M
(not noticed.) s
5 418 M
(Proposed Resolution:) s
5 407 M
(In 22.1.1 [lib.locale] and also in 22.1.1.3 [lib.locale.members],) s
5 396 M
(add "const" to the declaration of member combine:) s
5 374 M
(  template <class Facet> locale combine\(const locale& other\) const;) s
5 341 M
(--------------------------------------------------------------------------) s
5 330 M
(2. 22.1.1.3 [lib.locale.members] locale::name requirement inconsistent) s
5 308 M
(locale::name\(\) is described as returning a string that) s
5 297 M
(can be passed to a locale constructor, but there is no) s
5 286 M
(matching constructor.) s
5 264 M
(Proposed Resolution:) s
5 253 M
(In 22.1.1.3 [lib.locale.members], paragraph 5, replace) s
5 242 M
("locale\(name\(\)\)" with "locale\(name\(\).c_str\(\)\)".) s
5 209 M
(--------------------------------------------------------------------------) s
5 198 M
(3. 22.2.1.4, [lib.locale.ctype.byname.special] bad ctype_byname<char> decl) s
5 176 M
(The new virtual members ctype_byname<char>::do_widen and do_narrow) s
5 165 M
(did not get edited in properly.  Instead, the member do_widen appears) s
5 154 M
(four times, with wrong argument lists.) s
5 132 M
(Proposed Resolution:) s
5 121 M
(The correct declarations for the overloaded members do_narrow and) s
5 110 M
(do_widen should be copied from 22.2.1.3, [lib.facet.ctype.special].) s
5 66 M
(--------------------------------------------------------------------------) s
5 55 M
(4. 22.2.2.1.2 [lib.facet.num.get.virtuals] bad bool parsing) s
5 33 M
(This section describes the process of parsing a text boolean value) s
5 22 M
(from the input stream.  It does not say it recognizes either of the) s
5 11 M
(sequences "true" or "false" and returns the corresponding bool value.) s
_R
S
