5 781 M
(Instead, it says it recognizes only one of those sequences, and) s
5 770 M
(chooses which according to the received value of a reference argument) s
5 759 M
(intended for returning the result, and reports an error if the other) s
5 748 M
(sequence is found. \(!\)  Furthermore, it claims to get the names from) s
5 737 M
(the ctype<> facet rather than the numpunct<> facet, and it examines) s
5 726 M
(the "boolalpha" flag wrongly.  Finally, it doesn't define the value) s
5 715 M
("loc".) s
5 693 M
(In other words, the description is full of errors, and if the obvious) s
5 682 M
(errors are corrected, the result is unusable.) s
5 660 M
(I believe the correct algorithm is "as if":) s
5 638 M
(  // in, err, val, and str are arguments.) s
5 627 M
(  err = 0;) s
5 616 M
(  const numpunct<charT>& np = use_facet<numpunct<charT> >\(str.getloc\(\)\);) s
5 605 M
(  const string_type t = np.truename\(\);) s
5 594 M
(  const string_type f = np.falsename\(\);) s
5 583 M
(  bool tm = true; bool fm = true;) s
5 572 M
(  size_t pos = 0;) s
5 561 M
(  while \(tm && pos != t.size\(\) || fm && pos != f.size\(\)\) {) s
5 550 M
(    if \(in == end\) { err = str.eofbit; }) s
5 539 M
(    bool matched = false;) s
5 528 M
(    if \(tm && pos < t.size\(\)\) {) s
5 517 M
(      if \(!err && t[pos] == *in\) matched = true;) s
5 506 M
(      else tm = false;) s
5 495 M
(    }) s
5 484 M
(    if \(fm && pos < f.size\(\)\) {) s
5 473 M
(      if \(!err && f[pos] == *in\) matched = true;) s
5 462 M
(      else fm = false;) s
5 451 M
(    }) s
5 440 M
(    if \(matched\) { ++in; ++pos; }) s
5 429 M
(    if \(pos > t.size\(\)\) tm = false;) s
5 418 M
(    if \(pos > f.size\(\)\) fm = false;) s
5 407 M
(    if \(!tm && !fm\) { err |= str.failbit; return in; }) s
5 396 M
(  }) s
5 385 M
(  val = tm;) s
5 374 M
(  return in;) s
5 352 M
(Notice this works when the candidate strings are both empty, and) s
5 341 M
(when one is a substring of the other.  The proposed text below) s
5 330 M
(captures the logic of the code above.) s
5 308 M
(Proposed resolution:) s
5 297 M
(In 22.2.2.1.2 [lib.facet.num.get.virtuals], replace paragraphs 15 and) s
5 286 M
(16 as follows:) s
5 264 M
(  Otherwise target sequences are determined "as if" by calling the) s
5 253 M
(  members _falsename\(\)_ and _truename\(\)_ of the facet obtained by) s
5 242 M
(  _use_facet< numpunct<charT> >\(str.getloc\(\)\)_.  Successive characters) s
5 231 M
(  in the range _[in,end\)_ \(see [lib.sequence.reqmts]\) are obtained) s
5 220 M
(  and matched against corresponding positions in the target sequences) s
5 209 M
(  only as necessary to identify a unique match.  If a target sequence) s
5 198 M
(  is uniquely matched, _val_ is set to the corresponding value; or if) s
5 187 M
(  the targets are identical and matched, _val_ is set to _true_.) s
5 165 M
(  The _in_ iterator is always left pointing one position beyond the) s
5 154 M
(  last character successfully matched.  If _val_ is set, then err is) s
5 143 M
(  set to _str.goodbit_; or to _str.eofbit_ if, when seeking another) s
5 132 M
(  character to match, it is found that _\(in==end\)_.  If _val_ is not set,) s
5 121 M
(  then _err_ is set to _str.failbit_; or to _\(str.failbit|str.eofbit\)_) s
5 110 M
(  if the reason for the failure was that _\(in==end\)_.  [Example: for) s
5 99 M
(  targets _true_:"a" and _false_:"abb", the input sequence "a") s
5 88 M
(  yields _val==true_ and _err==str.eofbit_; the input sequence "abc") s
5 77 M
(  yields _err=str.failbit_, with _in_ ending at the 'c' element. For) s
5 66 M
(  targets _true_:"1" and _false_:"0", the input sequence "1" yields) s
5 55 M
(  _val==true_ and _err=str.goodbit_.  For empty targets \(""\), any) s
5 44 M
(  input sequence yields _val==true_ and _err==str.goodbit_. --end) s
5 33 M
(  example]) s
5 11 M
(Also: in the first line of paragraph 14, change "&&" to "&".) s
_R
S
