5 539 M
(11. 22.2.2.1.2 [lib.facet.num.get.virtuals] num_get overflow result) s
5 517 M
(The current description of numeric input does not account for the) s
5 506 M
(possibility of overflow.  This is an implicit result of changing) s
5 495 M
(the description to rely on the definition of scanf\(\) \(which fails) s
5 484 M
(to report overflow\), and conflicts with the documented behavior of) s
5 473 M
(traditional and current implementations.) s
5 451 M
(Users expect, when reading a character sequence that results in) s
5 440 M
(a value unrepresentable in the specified type, to have an error) s
5 429 M
(reported.  The standard as written does not permit this.) s
5 407 M
(Proposed Resolution:) s
5 396 M
(In 22.2.2.1.2 [lib.facet.num.get.virtuals], paragraph 11, second) s
5 385 M
(bullet item, change) s
5 363 M
(  The sequence of chars accumulated in stage 2 would have caused) s
5 352 M
(  scanf to report an input failure.) s
5 330 M
(to) s
5 308 M
(  The sequence of chars accumulated in stage 2 would have caused) s
5 297 M
(  scanf to report an input failure, or the value of the sequence) s
5 286 M
